	<title>Configuration file</title>

	<chapterinfo>
		<abstract>
			<para>In this file we go through the elements of a configuration
				file
				(conf.xml), making it possible (although optional) to change the
				static
				configuration and configure the environment of DataCleaner.
			</para>
		</abstract>
	</chapterinfo>

	<sect1>
		<title>Datastores</title>
		<sect1info>
			<abstract>
				<para>Datastores can be configured in the configuration file under
					the element &lt;datastore-catalog&gt;.</para>
			</abstract>
		</sect1info>

		<sect2>
			<title>Database (JDBC) connections</title>

			<para>Here are a few examples of common database types.</para>

			<tip>
				<para>The DataCleaner GUI makes it a lot easier to figure out the
					url (connection string) and driver class part of the connection
					properties. It's a good place to start if you don't know these
					properties already.</para>
			</tip>

			<para>MySQL</para>
			<programlisting lang="xml">
				&lt;jdbc-datastore name="MySQL datastore"&gt;
					&lt;url&gt;jdbc:mysql://hostname:3306/database&lt;/url&gt;
					&lt;driver&gt;com.mysql.jdbc.Driver&lt;/driver&gt;
					&lt;username&gt;username&lt;/username&gt;
					&lt;password&gt;password&lt;/password&gt;
				&lt;/jdbc-datastore&gt;
			</programlisting>
			
			<para>Oracle</para>
			<programlisting lang="xml">
				&lt;jdbc-datastore name="Oracle datastore"&gt;
					&lt;url&gt;jdbc:oracle:thin:@hostname:1521:sid&lt;/url&gt;
					&lt;driver&gt;oracle.jdbc.OracleDriver&lt;/driver&gt;
					&lt;username&gt;username&lt;/username&gt;
					&lt;password&gt;password&lt;/password&gt;
				&lt;/jdbc-datastore&gt;
			</programlisting>
			
			<para>Microsoft SQL Server</para>
			<programlisting lang="xml">
				&lt;jdbc-datastore name="MS SQL Server datastore"&gt;
					&lt;url&gt;jdbc:jtds:sqlserver://hostname/database;useUnicode=true;characterEncoding=UTF-8&lt;/url&gt;
					&lt;driver&gt;net.sourceforge.jtds.jdbc.Driver&lt;/driver&gt;
					&lt;username&gt;username&lt;/username&gt;
					&lt;password&gt;password&lt;/password&gt;
				&lt;/jdbc-datastore&gt;
			</programlisting>
		</sect2>

